Arrange rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into sticks. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were 3 inches long and 1/3 inch thick).

Toss potatoes and carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @oil{a large drizzle}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(minced).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper.

> Swap in pork chops for chicken if preferred.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}, and 1/2 cup water.

> Use all the thyme and 1 cup water for 4 servings.

Heat pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add garlic, shallot, and @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} to hot pan. Cook, stirring, until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{10-15%seconds}.

Stir in @butter{2%tablespoon} until melted.

Add @flour{1%tablespoon} and cook, stirring constantly, until lightly browned, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk in stock concentrate mixture and bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> For a thinner sauce, add a splash of water.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together @mixed greens{2%ounce}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, and as much @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon} as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, frites, and salad between #plates{}. Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.